han one kind of fruit </div><div class="t mbd x3 h27 y8e6 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">at the same time? James 3: 10-12. • How is this same </div><div class="t m3bd x3 h27 y94d ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">principle illustrated in a fountain? </div><div class="t m1d2 x26 h27 y1396 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">7. </div><div class="t me4e x64 h27 y1396 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What application is made of this principle to our </div><div class="t m7e6 x3 h27 y58b ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christian experience ? Luke 6: 43-46; Matt. 12: 33-35. </div><div class="t m1d5 x71 h27 y40d ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">8. </div><div class="t m22b x64 h27 y40d ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What dispositicai is made of trees that do not yield </div><div class="t m47e x3 h27 y1a8 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">good fruit? Matt. 3: 8-10. </div><div class="t m127 x26 h27 yd34 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">9. </div><div class="t m9d3 x64 h27 yd34 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How only can we bear good fruit? John 15:4, 5. </div><div class="t me4 x17 h27 y3c2 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">10. </div><div class="t m106e x64 h27 y3c2 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What is the result of truly abiding in Christ? </div><div class="t mb7c xbd h27 y2d ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 7; 8. </div><div class="t me4 x11 h27 y42c ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">11. </div><div class="t m3d1 x64 h27 y42c ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What is done with fruitless branches ? Verses 2, 6. </div><div class="t me4 x11 h27 y1614 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">12. </div><div class="t m37d x64 h27 y852 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What did the Savioni do with the fruitless fig tree? </div><div class="t m34e xc4 h27 y85 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• </div><div class="t m2d1 x3 h27 y1397 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mark 11: 1144, 20, 21. Note 2. </div><div class="t m107e x17 h27 y3a ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">13. What parable spoken by the Saviour&apos; illustrates this </div><div class="t m2fb xbd h27 y87 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">matter ? • Luke 13: 6-9. </div><div class="t m2cc x28 h21 y